gov.ca.dsm2.input.model
Class Channel

java.lang.Object
  gov.ca.dsm2.input.model.Channel
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Channel
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

In DSM2 a channel is an entity representing a stream with a in stream length getLength(), roughness coefficient (mannings n) getMannings(), dispersion factor getDispersion() for water quality constituents It is defined by an id getId() and its two end nodes, up node getUpNodeId() and down node getDownNodeId(). It also has a number of xsections getXsections() and contains the gis getLatLngPoints() information to demarcate the internal points
